autoclean.mixins.signal_processing.pylossless.PyLosslessMixin#

class autoclean.mixins.signal_processing.pylossless.PyLosslessMixin[source]#

Bases: object

Mixin class providing PyLossless functionality for autoclean tasks.

step_custom_pylossless_pipeline(config, eog_channel='E25', stage_name='post_pylossless')[source]#

Run PyLossless pipeline on the data.

This method runs the PyLossless pipeline on the input data. It includes steps for filtering, flagging bad channels, and flagging bad epochs.

Parameters:
configdict

The configuration dictionary for the autoclean pipeline.

eog_channelstr | None, optional

The channel name of the EOG channel. Default is “E25”. This parameter is used to specify the channel referenced for eog specific ICA. If None, no EOG channel will be used.

stage_namestr, optional

The name of the stage for saving and metadata. Default is “post_pylossless”.

Returns:
pipelineinstance of ll.LosslessPipeline

The PyLossless pipeline object.

pipeline.rawinstance of mne.io.Raw

The raw data object with PyLossless processing applied.

See also

pylossless.LosslessPipeline

For more information on the PyLossless pipeline

Notes

This method is a wrapper around the PyLossless pipeline. It includes a mixture of Pylossless and Autoclean functions in order to provide a comprehensive pipeline.

step_get_pylossless_pipeline(autoclean_dict)[source]#

Create a PyLossless pipeline object.

Parameters:
autoclean_dictdict

The configuration dictionary for the autoclean pipeline.

Returns:
pipelineinstance of ll.LosslessPipeline

The PyLossless pipeline object.

See also

pylossless.LosslessPipeline

For more information on the PyLossless pipeline

Notes

This method is used as the first step in creating a custom PyLossless pipeline. It will read the raw data in the BIDS path and create a PyLossless pipeline object. So it is important that the save_to_bids step is run before this step.
